WEBVTT

00:02.959 --> 00:04.613
- ♪ Hey, here comes Sunny
keeping it fun ♪

00:04.743 --> 00:06.310
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:06.441 --> 00:08.443
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:08.573 --> 00:10.140
♪ Hey

00:10.271 --> 00:11.968
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:12.099 --> 00:13.709
♪ Hair styling
with her best friends ♪

00:13.839 --> 00:16.059
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:16.190 --> 00:19.193
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny Day

00:19.323 --> 00:21.499
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:21.630 --> 00:23.284
- Whoo-hoo!

00:23.414 --> 00:28.028
- ♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:31.074
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.205 --> 00:33.468
♪ Having a sunny, sunny day

00:33.598 --> 00:34.599
- Hoo-hoo!

00:41.258 --> 00:43.565
- That must have been
our biggest salon supply

00:43.695 --> 00:45.349
shopping spree ever!

00:45.480 --> 00:48.396
- There's the park.
We're almost home.

00:48.526 --> 00:51.747
- [sighs]
No more shopping.

00:51.877 --> 00:54.837
Must sleep.
So tired.

00:54.967 --> 00:56.708
- I hope we remembered
everything.

00:56.839 --> 00:58.232
- Let's see.

00:58.362 --> 01:00.582
Shampoo, hair spray, gels...
- [snoring]

01:00.712 --> 01:01.887
[gasps]

01:02.018 --> 01:04.455
That's right!
Awesome new hair gels.

01:04.586 --> 01:06.849
So sparkly.

01:06.979 --> 01:09.112
- And all those new ribbons.

01:09.243 --> 01:10.983
So silky.

01:11.114 --> 01:12.072
- Whoa!
- Hold on!

01:12.202 --> 01:13.073
- Whoa!

01:13.203 --> 01:14.117
Oof!

01:14.248 --> 01:15.771
- Oops. Sorry.

01:15.901 --> 01:17.686
Oh, did we remember
to buy wigs?

01:17.816 --> 01:19.296
- [barks]
We sure did!

01:19.427 --> 01:21.385
[laughter]

01:21.516 --> 01:23.953
- Oh, oh! Let's stop
for ice cream at the boardwalk.

01:24.084 --> 01:26.260
- New hair supplies,
ice cream...

01:26.390 --> 01:28.044
This day just keeps
getting better.

01:28.175 --> 01:29.393
- [laughs]

01:29.524 --> 01:31.830
Next stop, the boardwalk!

01:31.961 --> 01:34.833
[upbeat music]

01:34.964 --> 01:41.013
♪

01:41.144 --> 01:42.406
- Hmm, let's see.

01:42.537 --> 01:44.408
Do I want strawberry swirl,

01:44.539 --> 01:46.106
or chocolate cheesecake...

01:46.236 --> 01:48.325
[gasps]
Or banana berry?

01:48.456 --> 01:50.458
It's so hard to choose.

01:50.588 --> 01:53.069
- Well, maybe you should get
all of them.

01:53.200 --> 01:56.116
- Mm, that's too much,
even for me.

01:56.246 --> 01:58.466
- [laughs]
- ♪ I play my guitar

01:58.596 --> 02:02.296
♪ 'Cause I like its sound...
- Wow, that voice.

02:02.426 --> 02:03.949
It's beautiful.

02:04.080 --> 02:05.864
But where is it coming from?

02:05.995 --> 02:09.955
- ♪ Soft, gentle rhythms,
they make me want to sing ♪

02:10.086 --> 02:14.525
♪ I really love simple things

02:14.656 --> 02:15.526
- Johnny Ray?

02:15.657 --> 02:17.049
- Oh! Hi, Sunny.

02:17.180 --> 02:18.573
- Your voice...

02:18.703 --> 02:20.140
it's beautiful.

02:20.270 --> 02:21.706
- Aww.

02:21.837 --> 02:24.405
I was just playing a little
tune with Suzette here.

02:24.535 --> 02:25.971
She keeps the beat.

02:26.102 --> 02:28.060
- [whinnying]

02:28.191 --> 02:31.151
- You're both really good.

02:31.281 --> 02:33.153
The others have got to hearthis.

02:33.283 --> 02:35.938
[gasps]
You could be a country star.

02:36.068 --> 02:37.940
- A country star?
- [whinnies]

02:38.070 --> 02:40.769
Oh, I just like singing
for Suzette.

02:40.899 --> 02:42.074
- But a talent like yours

02:42.205 --> 02:43.772
should be shared
with the world.

02:43.902 --> 02:46.340
[gasps] We could put on
a show tonight!

02:46.470 --> 02:49.125
- Tonight?
What--I'm not sure I'm ready

02:49.256 --> 02:50.909
for anyone else
to hear my singing.

02:51.040 --> 02:52.781
- But you have to!

02:52.911 --> 02:55.523
And you too, Suzette.
- [neighs]

02:55.653 --> 02:58.656
- [laughs]
Well, okay, Sunny.

02:58.787 --> 03:00.049
I trust you.

03:00.180 --> 03:01.659
If you say I should do a show,

03:01.790 --> 03:03.183
I'll do a show,

03:03.313 --> 03:07.012
as long as it's small, simple,
and low-key.

03:07.143 --> 03:08.666
Nothing big or fancy,

03:08.797 --> 03:11.887
just me and Suzette singing
for a few friends.

03:12.017 --> 03:13.367
- Absolutely.

03:13.497 --> 03:16.021
It's going to be
the best little show ever,

03:16.152 --> 03:17.022
you'll see.

03:17.153 --> 03:18.372
Hmm.

03:18.502 --> 03:19.416
There's lots to do.

03:19.547 --> 03:20.722
Let's go to the salon.

03:20.852 --> 03:22.550
It's where I do some
of my best planning.

03:22.680 --> 03:23.899
- Whoa!

03:24.029 --> 03:26.510
- Come on, Suzette.
- [whinnies]

03:26.641 --> 03:28.120
[bell jingles]

03:28.251 --> 03:29.861
- This is gonna be fun.

03:31.298 --> 03:32.777
- So what are we doing, Sunny?

03:32.908 --> 03:34.083
- Yeah, what's up?

03:34.214 --> 03:36.607
♪

03:36.738 --> 03:37.739
- [whinnies]

03:37.869 --> 03:41.177
♪

03:41.308 --> 03:43.266
- So we're gonna stage a show

03:43.397 --> 03:45.529
for Johnny Ray to sing
and play his guitar...

03:45.660 --> 03:46.574
tonight!

03:46.704 --> 03:48.053
- Tonight?

03:48.184 --> 03:51.970
That'll take a lot
of organizing.

03:52.101 --> 03:54.016
Oh, yay!
[giggles]

03:54.146 --> 03:56.236
Organizing is sort of my thing.

03:56.366 --> 03:59.326
So let's start the show
promptly at sunset.

03:59.456 --> 04:02.764
- [laughs] I can't believe
I'm gonna be in a show.

04:02.894 --> 04:05.288
It's gonna be small, simple,
and low-key,

04:05.419 --> 04:06.637
right, Sunny?

04:06.768 --> 04:08.596
- Whatever you say, Johnny Ray.

04:08.726 --> 04:10.032
You're the star.

04:10.162 --> 04:11.947
I'm thinking Rox
can paint the set

04:12.077 --> 04:13.296
with her new hair chalks.

04:13.427 --> 04:14.950
- Yeah, they're so colorful.

04:15.080 --> 04:16.908
- And Blair can accessorize.

04:17.039 --> 04:20.390
- A little gingham ribbon
goes a long way.

04:20.521 --> 04:22.740
- [gasps]
What about me, Sunny?

04:22.871 --> 04:25.482
- You can be
my helpful assistant.

04:25.613 --> 04:27.179
- That's very me.

04:27.310 --> 04:28.964
- And I'll do everything else,

04:29.094 --> 04:30.139
apart from sing.

04:30.270 --> 04:31.967
Johnny Ray can take care
of that.

04:32.097 --> 04:35.275
- We had no idea
you could even sing.

04:35.405 --> 04:37.102
- Yes, well...
- No time to waste.

04:37.233 --> 04:38.800
There's so much to do.
- Wait.

04:38.930 --> 04:41.281
Shouldn't we get a bunch
of people for the audience?

04:41.411 --> 04:42.978
- A bunch of people?

04:43.108 --> 04:45.328
- [laughs]
Let's see.

04:45.459 --> 04:48.810
How can we let everyone know
about the concert?

04:48.940 --> 04:50.464
[gasps]
I know!

04:50.594 --> 04:51.856
What better way
to spread the word

04:51.987 --> 04:53.205
about a country concert

04:53.336 --> 04:56.774
than with some
country hairstyles?

04:56.905 --> 04:59.386
Let's give you braids
with some country ribbon.

04:59.516 --> 05:01.126
♪

05:01.257 --> 05:03.738
Braid in the ribbon like so.

05:03.868 --> 05:05.043
You're right, Blair.

05:05.174 --> 05:07.568
A little gingham does go
a long way.

05:07.698 --> 05:10.048
- It looks amazing.

05:10.179 --> 05:11.920
- Your turn, Rox.

05:12.050 --> 05:15.793
This looks great
woven into your braids, Rox.

05:15.924 --> 05:16.925
Done.

05:17.055 --> 05:19.449
We look great.

05:19.580 --> 05:21.146
- Yee-haw!
- [giggles]

05:21.277 --> 05:22.887
- Now it's my turn.

05:23.018 --> 05:25.586
This'll do the trick.

05:25.716 --> 05:27.675
Bring it across
and pull it through.

05:27.805 --> 05:33.550
♪

05:33.681 --> 05:35.944
There. Perfect.

05:36.074 --> 05:37.467
Doodle!

05:37.598 --> 05:38.947
Can't forget you.

05:39.077 --> 05:42.429
♪

05:42.559 --> 05:44.735
- Oh, thanks, Sunny!

05:44.866 --> 05:46.476
- Johnny Ray!

05:46.607 --> 05:48.260
Now we're ready
to tell everyone

05:48.391 --> 05:49.566
about your country concert.

05:49.697 --> 05:51.002
- Everyone?

05:51.133 --> 05:52.917
I thought we were going to
keep this small,

05:53.048 --> 05:54.745
just us, between friends?

05:54.876 --> 05:56.834
- And have the rest of the town
miss out?

05:56.965 --> 05:58.793
[laughs]
You're way too good.

05:58.923 --> 06:01.752
- Thanks...I guess?

06:01.883 --> 06:04.320
- Okay, smile!

06:04.451 --> 06:06.844
Definitely one
for the Style Files.

06:06.975 --> 06:10.326
You're the star, so maybe you
should stay here and practice.

06:10.457 --> 06:14.417
- And maybe you can get Suzette
to stop eating our magazines.

06:14.548 --> 06:15.984
- Oh, Suzette.

06:16.114 --> 06:16.985
[all laugh]

06:17.115 --> 06:18.073
- Okay, team.

06:18.203 --> 06:20.292
Ready. Set.

06:20.423 --> 06:22.730
all: Gear up and go!

06:22.860 --> 06:29.911
♪

06:31.695 --> 06:32.566
- [whinnies]

06:32.696 --> 06:34.045
- It's okay, Suzette.

06:34.176 --> 06:36.265
Sunny said it'll just be
a little show.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.746
Small, simple, and low-key.

06:38.876 --> 06:41.618
[sighs]

06:41.923 --> 06:44.665
[upbeat music]

06:44.795 --> 06:47.276
- Whoa, Sunny!
Awesome hairstyle.

06:47.407 --> 06:49.583
- Yeah, cool.
- Thanks.

06:49.713 --> 06:51.889
Country braids
for a country concert.

06:52.020 --> 06:53.151
We're getting the word out

06:53.282 --> 06:54.849
about Johnny Ray's show
tonight.

06:54.979 --> 06:58.374
- It'll be a country music
concert you'll never forget.

06:58.505 --> 07:00.594
- Probably the best show ever.

07:00.724 --> 07:02.334
- Wow, we'll be there.

07:02.465 --> 07:04.119
Bye, guys.
See you later.

07:04.249 --> 07:05.642
- See you later.

07:05.773 --> 07:08.689
[spoons tapping in rhythm]

07:08.819 --> 07:09.994
♪

07:10.125 --> 07:11.692
- Hi, Cindy.

07:11.822 --> 07:14.303
I've never heard spoons
sound like that before.

07:14.434 --> 07:17.393
- [laughs] Well, if there's one
thing we have in the bakery,

07:17.524 --> 07:19.090
it's spoons.

07:19.221 --> 07:21.223
Ooh, I love your hair.

07:21.353 --> 07:22.616
Trying something new?

07:22.746 --> 07:24.008
- We're letting everyone know

07:24.139 --> 07:25.967
about Johnny Ray's concerttonight.

07:26.097 --> 07:29.449
- And what's better than braids
for a country music concert?

07:29.579 --> 07:32.321
- Ooh, I love country music.

07:32.452 --> 07:34.018
- Hey, I have an idea!

07:34.149 --> 07:35.977
You could play your spoons
in the show.

07:36.107 --> 07:38.153
- Really? Yippee!

07:38.283 --> 07:39.807
Yippee-yi-yay!

07:39.937 --> 07:41.156
I'll see you there.

07:41.286 --> 07:42.462
- See you later.
- Bye, Cindy.

07:42.592 --> 07:44.464
- Have a sunny day!

07:45.508 --> 07:48.337
[vases softly ringing]

07:48.468 --> 07:52.254
♪

07:52.384 --> 07:54.735
Wow, that sounds great, Peter.

07:54.865 --> 07:57.215
- Oh, thanks, Sunny.

07:57.346 --> 07:59.566
Who knew I had a musical gift?

07:59.696 --> 08:02.351
- You know, we've got a guitar,

08:02.482 --> 08:04.005
and we've got spoons.

08:04.135 --> 08:07.443
I'm sure Johnny Ray would love
for you to be in the show too.

08:07.574 --> 08:09.793
- A show?
With Johnny Ray?

08:09.924 --> 08:11.752
Me? I'd love to!

08:11.882 --> 08:13.362
- Great!

08:13.493 --> 08:16.670
Oh, this is going to be
the best show ever.

08:16.800 --> 08:20.151
- It sure will.
- Just one question.

08:20.282 --> 08:21.675
Where's it going to be?

08:21.805 --> 08:24.504
- I've already thought of that.

08:25.722 --> 08:28.725
And this is our stage.

08:28.856 --> 08:30.945
- Well, the stage looks
pretty busy, Sunny.

08:31.075 --> 08:33.991
I'm not sure anyone else
would have room to perform.

08:34.122 --> 08:37.168
♪

08:37.299 --> 08:39.562
[laughs]
My mistake.

08:39.693 --> 08:41.259
- Looks like the ballerinas
are practicing

08:41.390 --> 08:42.304
for their next recital.

08:42.434 --> 08:44.001
- [gasps]
That's it!

08:44.132 --> 08:45.612
You're a genius, Rox.

08:45.742 --> 08:47.701
- Yes, I am!

08:47.831 --> 08:49.137
Uh, wait.
I am?

08:49.267 --> 08:51.052
- I'll ask the ballerinas

08:51.182 --> 08:53.445
to be Johnny Ray's
backup dancers.

08:53.576 --> 08:56.579
- Wow! That is a great idea.

08:56.710 --> 08:58.494
I am a genius.

08:59.669 --> 09:01.845
- Of course we'll help out,
Sunny.

09:01.976 --> 09:03.455
We'd love to be
in Johnny Ray's concert.

09:03.586 --> 09:05.022
- Thanks, Hannah.

09:05.153 --> 09:07.329
I really want to make his show
special for him.

09:07.459 --> 09:09.157
- Happy to help!

09:09.287 --> 09:10.462
- Whoa, whoa!

09:10.593 --> 09:11.855
- [laughing]

09:11.986 --> 09:14.423
- Cindy, Peter, ballerinas...

09:14.554 --> 09:17.469
This is turning into
a really big show.

09:17.600 --> 09:19.515
- Yeah! So what's next?

09:19.646 --> 09:22.779
- We need to make this stage
fit for a star.

09:22.910 --> 09:24.607
♪

09:24.738 --> 09:26.870
- Back a bit.
A bit more.

09:27.001 --> 09:27.828
A bit less!

09:27.958 --> 09:29.133
- Whoa! Oof!

09:29.264 --> 09:30.091
both: Oh!

09:30.221 --> 09:31.179
- I'm okay!

09:31.309 --> 09:33.268
- Oops! Sorry, Doodle.

09:33.398 --> 09:35.531
- Hi, Sunny.
- We're not too early, are we?

09:35.662 --> 09:37.881
- If you don't mind helping us
set up,

09:38.012 --> 09:40.492
you're right on time.

09:40.623 --> 09:42.538
[guitar strumming]

09:42.669 --> 09:44.322
- I wonder what's keeping them.

09:44.453 --> 09:45.802
I mean, how long could it take

09:45.933 --> 09:48.762
to put together
a small, simple show?

09:48.892 --> 09:50.546
[upbeat music]

09:50.677 --> 09:51.721
- [exclaiming]

09:51.852 --> 09:53.114
Clear the way!

09:53.244 --> 09:54.202
- Doodle?

09:54.332 --> 09:55.682
- Oh, whoa!

09:55.812 --> 09:57.422
[groans]

09:57.553 --> 09:58.859
- Are you okay?

09:58.989 --> 10:01.731
- Yep!
But I think I broke something.

10:01.862 --> 10:02.993
- [laughs]

10:03.124 --> 10:04.081
- Yes.

10:04.212 --> 10:06.693
♪

10:06.823 --> 10:08.999
[humming]

10:09.130 --> 10:11.567
♪

10:11.698 --> 10:12.873
- Oh!

10:13.003 --> 10:14.918
- [giggles]

10:15.049 --> 10:17.355
- [gasps]
Not the vases!

10:17.486 --> 10:19.619
They're finely tuned
instruments.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.838
[spoons tapping,
vases ringing]

10:21.969 --> 10:24.319
- What do you think, Doodle?

10:24.449 --> 10:26.060
- Wow bow-wow!

10:26.190 --> 10:28.758
- It is pretty spectacular.

10:28.889 --> 10:32.893
- I know Johnny Ray said small,
simple, and low-key,

10:33.023 --> 10:36.592
but a talent like his deserves
a really big show.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.159
- It's big all right.

10:38.289 --> 10:39.769
- Will you get Johnny Ray
and Suzette?

10:39.900 --> 10:41.597
It's almost time for the show,

10:41.728 --> 10:46.341
and I've got one more
starry surprise for Johnny Ray.

10:46.471 --> 10:48.125
[van beeps]

10:48.256 --> 10:51.520
- Ha! There he is, our star!

10:51.651 --> 10:52.608
- Great!

10:52.739 --> 10:54.479
Just in time for your makeover.

10:54.610 --> 10:56.438
- Just in time for my what now?

10:56.568 --> 10:57.439
Whoa!

10:57.569 --> 10:58.701
- [whinnies]

10:58.832 --> 11:00.834
- Your makeover!
- [gasps]

11:00.964 --> 11:03.053
- If you're going to be a star,

11:03.184 --> 11:05.534
you should look like a star.

11:05.665 --> 11:06.927
- But--
- We'll have you good to go

11:07.057 --> 11:08.276
in no time.

11:08.406 --> 11:10.278
I just need
my number four comb,

11:10.408 --> 11:11.714
some super stick hairspray,

11:11.845 --> 11:13.107
and glitter.

11:13.237 --> 11:14.586
- Glitter?
[laughs]

11:14.717 --> 11:16.327
Okay.

11:16.458 --> 11:19.330
As long as we're going to keep
my makeover and the show

11:19.461 --> 11:21.593
small, simple, and low-key.

11:21.724 --> 11:24.379
- Let's get to work.

11:24.509 --> 11:27.425
♪

11:27.556 --> 11:29.253
Ooh, I like that.

11:29.384 --> 11:31.734
I think we can make this
even better...

11:31.865 --> 11:34.128
with color!

11:34.258 --> 11:35.738
And some glitter.

11:37.392 --> 11:39.046
Oh, perfect.

11:39.176 --> 11:41.091
Let's show Suzette.

11:41.222 --> 11:43.137
♪

11:43.267 --> 11:44.791
Ta-da!

11:44.921 --> 11:46.096
- [whinnies]

11:46.227 --> 11:48.142
- Hi, Sunny.
We got the flowers

11:48.272 --> 11:50.666
for Johnny Ray's dressing room,
just like you asked.

11:50.797 --> 11:52.929
- Mmm, and the chocolates.

11:53.060 --> 11:55.932
Well, there were chocolates.

11:56.063 --> 11:58.413
- Hey, Rox, Blair,
what do you think

11:58.543 --> 12:02.373
of Friendly Falls' newest
country music star?

12:02.504 --> 12:06.029
- Amazing, Sunny!
But where's Johnny Ray?

12:06.160 --> 12:08.597
- [laughs]
This is Johnny Ray.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.251
- [chuckles]
- What do you think?

12:10.381 --> 12:11.948
both: Wow!

12:12.079 --> 12:15.909
- Uh, that's one bold
style statement.

12:16.039 --> 12:19.347
- But does it say
"I'm a star"?

12:19.477 --> 12:21.784
- It doesn't just say it.

12:21.915 --> 12:23.394
It shouts it.

12:23.525 --> 12:26.049
- I'm not sure it's me.

12:26.180 --> 12:27.268
What do you think, Suzette?

12:27.398 --> 12:28.748
- [neighs]

12:28.878 --> 12:31.838
- It's a big look
for your big show.

12:31.968 --> 12:33.753
- Big? How big?

12:35.189 --> 12:36.886
- This big!

12:37.017 --> 12:38.583
Great, huh?

12:38.714 --> 12:41.195
- But I thought we were gonna
keep things small.

12:41.325 --> 12:42.936
- It's sort of small,

12:43.066 --> 12:44.502
except for the ballerinas

12:44.633 --> 12:45.808
and the spoons

12:45.939 --> 12:47.157
and the vases.

12:47.288 --> 12:49.551
- Sunny! We've got a problem
with the doves

12:49.681 --> 12:51.292
you wanted to release
for the big finale?

12:51.422 --> 12:53.424
As in, I can't find any doves.

12:53.555 --> 12:55.905
- Oh, okay, Doodle.
Let me see what I can do.

12:56.036 --> 12:59.300
I'll be right back, superstar.

12:59.430 --> 13:01.563
This is going to be huge!

13:01.693 --> 13:02.651
[giggles]

13:02.782 --> 13:05.219
- This is gonna be a big show,

13:05.349 --> 13:07.134
a too-big show.

13:07.264 --> 13:10.180
- [whinnies]

13:10.311 --> 13:13.053
- Thanks, Suzette.
I knew you'd understand.

13:13.183 --> 13:16.273
I'm leaving.
Say sorry to Sunny for me.

13:16.404 --> 13:18.580
♪

13:18.710 --> 13:20.887
- Okay, so, Blair,
status update?

13:21.017 --> 13:22.540
- The lasers are set,

13:22.671 --> 13:24.673
the ballerinas are practicing
their do-si-do,

13:24.804 --> 13:26.631
and Doodle's moving
those old boxes

13:26.762 --> 13:28.459
from that end of the stage

13:28.590 --> 13:30.897
to this end of the stage.

13:31.027 --> 13:32.942
- This is really hard work.

13:33.073 --> 13:34.944
- [grunts]

13:35.075 --> 13:36.337
- Thanks for helping, Rox.

13:36.467 --> 13:38.252
- Huh?[sighs]

13:38.382 --> 13:39.819
- [laughs]
- Just in time

13:39.949 --> 13:41.646
for a final sound check.

13:41.777 --> 13:44.432
- Thanks, Blair.
For that, we need Johnny Ray.

13:44.562 --> 13:46.564
Where is Johnny Ray?

13:46.695 --> 13:47.870
- I'll track him down.

13:48.001 --> 13:50.090
I'm an expert sniffer dog.

13:50.220 --> 13:52.309
♪

13:52.440 --> 13:54.181
- Johnny Ray?
- Johnny Ray?

13:54.311 --> 13:55.835
♪

13:55.965 --> 13:58.881
- Suzette, do you know
where Johnny Ray is?

13:59.012 --> 14:02.015
- [neighing]

14:04.104 --> 14:05.453
- [gasps]

14:05.583 --> 14:06.671
- No, I got nothing.

14:06.802 --> 14:08.891
- It's okay, I speak pony.

14:09.022 --> 14:10.980
- So what did Suzette say?

14:11.111 --> 14:13.113
- Um, the short answer?

14:13.243 --> 14:15.463
Johnny Ray is really,
really sorry,

14:15.593 --> 14:17.291
but he can't do the show.

14:17.421 --> 14:18.553
He left.

14:18.683 --> 14:20.207
- [gasps]

14:22.209 --> 14:23.384
- Johnny Ray's a no-show

14:23.514 --> 14:25.255
at his own show?

14:25.386 --> 14:27.649
- And the audience
will be arriving soon.

14:27.779 --> 14:29.912
- I--I don't understand.

14:30.043 --> 14:31.783
Why would Johnny Ray leave?

14:31.914 --> 14:34.047
We have backup dancers
and spoons

14:34.177 --> 14:35.918
and Peter playing
his glass vases,

14:36.049 --> 14:39.008
and it was going to be
the biggest show ever.

14:40.314 --> 14:41.619
Oh.

14:41.750 --> 14:44.622
But that's not what Johnny Ray
wanted.

14:44.753 --> 14:47.451
Oh, it's all my fault.

14:47.582 --> 14:51.499
He said he wanted small,
simple, and low-key,

14:51.629 --> 14:53.631
and I didn't listen.

14:53.762 --> 14:55.372
No wonder he left.

14:55.503 --> 14:57.635
I have to make this right,

14:57.766 --> 14:59.855
and that means
I have to find Johnny Ray.

14:59.986 --> 15:01.639
Suzette, can you help?

15:01.770 --> 15:02.684
- [whinnies]

15:02.814 --> 15:03.946
- Suzette says,

15:04.077 --> 15:05.861
Johnny Ray
is sorry he had to leave

15:05.992 --> 15:08.603
but she has a pretty good idea
where he might be.

15:08.733 --> 15:10.605
He's her best friend,
so she knows him really well.

15:10.735 --> 15:12.041
So follow her!

15:12.172 --> 15:14.739
- She said all that
with a...neigh?

15:14.870 --> 15:15.784
- Yep.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.177
- Come on, Suzette!

15:17.307 --> 15:18.743
Let's find Johnny Ray.

15:18.874 --> 15:21.485
♪

15:21.616 --> 15:24.097
- [neighing]

15:24.227 --> 15:28.362
♪

15:28.492 --> 15:29.711
- Thanks, Suzette.

15:29.841 --> 15:31.800
I'll take it from here.

15:31.931 --> 15:33.280
Johnny Ray...

15:33.410 --> 15:34.629
- Hi, Sunny.

15:34.759 --> 15:36.674
I guess you're wondering
why I'm here

15:36.805 --> 15:38.067
and not at the show.

15:38.198 --> 15:40.591
- No, I think I know why.

15:40.722 --> 15:42.637
You've been trying
to tell me all day

15:42.767 --> 15:44.465
what sort of show you wanted.

15:44.595 --> 15:47.729
- Our little show
became a really big one.

15:47.859 --> 15:50.906
Plus, I didn't feel like me
anymore.

15:51.037 --> 15:52.473
- I'm sorry, Johnny Ray.

15:52.603 --> 15:54.692
I broke my number one rule:

15:54.823 --> 15:57.826
Always listen to what
your customer wants.

15:57.957 --> 16:00.568
I just wanted to put on a show
as big as your talent.

16:00.698 --> 16:02.352
- It's okay, Sunny.

16:02.483 --> 16:04.528
I know you were only trying
to help.

16:04.659 --> 16:08.228
- If I promise no spoons
and no ballerinas,

16:08.358 --> 16:10.534
would you give me a chance
to make things right?

16:10.665 --> 16:15.539
♪

16:15.670 --> 16:16.845
- Of course I can.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.151
What's the plan?

16:18.281 --> 16:20.588
- First,
let's get Johnny Ray back.

16:20.718 --> 16:22.155
The real Johnny Ray.

16:22.285 --> 16:24.070
And that means a makeover...

16:24.200 --> 16:25.593
in reverse.

16:25.723 --> 16:28.422
♪

16:28.552 --> 16:30.728
Oh, let me just...

16:30.859 --> 16:32.339
on second thought,

16:32.469 --> 16:34.210
you're fine
just the way you are.

16:34.341 --> 16:35.777
- [neighs]

16:36.952 --> 16:39.128
[whinnies]

16:39.259 --> 16:40.956
- You got it, Suzette.

16:41.087 --> 16:42.653
She says we better get going.

16:42.784 --> 16:44.003
It's showtime.

16:44.133 --> 16:45.569
- [neighs]

16:46.788 --> 16:48.572
- After you.

16:48.703 --> 16:50.270
♪

16:50.400 --> 16:51.358
both: Huh?

16:51.488 --> 16:53.925
- That's a lot of traffic.

16:54.056 --> 16:56.580
They're probably heading
to your concert.

16:56.711 --> 16:59.670
- Looks like we'll never
get back in time now.

16:59.801 --> 17:01.803
- [whinnies]

17:01.933 --> 17:03.326
- Never say never.

17:03.457 --> 17:06.851
♪

17:06.982 --> 17:09.376
Four legs are definitely
quicker than four wheels

17:09.506 --> 17:10.768
in this traffic.

17:10.899 --> 17:12.335
- Giddy up, Suzette!

17:13.989 --> 17:15.382
Hang on, Sunny!

17:15.512 --> 17:18.211
♪

17:18.341 --> 17:20.082
Yee-haw!
- Whoa!

17:20.213 --> 17:21.866
[together] Hey, hey, hey!
We want Johnny Ray!

17:21.997 --> 17:23.172
- When's the show?

17:23.303 --> 17:25.957
- Yeah, we want Johnny Ray!

17:26.088 --> 17:27.829
- The crowd
is getting restless.

17:27.959 --> 17:29.352
They want Johnny Ray.

17:29.483 --> 17:31.050
- What are we gonna do?

17:31.180 --> 17:33.313
- Cindy, Peter, ballerinas?

17:33.443 --> 17:35.141
It's showtime.

17:35.271 --> 17:36.751
- Oh, we're running outof time.

17:36.881 --> 17:38.840
- Don't worry,
I know a shortcut.

17:38.970 --> 17:41.712
♪

17:41.843 --> 17:43.453
Whoa!

17:43.584 --> 17:45.020
That's too high, Sunny.

17:45.151 --> 17:46.848
- I've got an idea.

17:46.978 --> 17:49.372
Some ribbon, a knot...

17:49.503 --> 17:51.287
Nice and tight.

17:51.418 --> 17:56.118
♪

17:56.249 --> 17:57.119
- Yee-haw!

17:57.250 --> 17:58.338
Whoo-hoo!

17:58.468 --> 18:00.079
That was awesome!

18:00.209 --> 18:02.037
♪

18:02.168 --> 18:05.040
[spoons tapping,
vases ringing]

18:05.171 --> 18:09.305
♪

18:09.436 --> 18:11.525
[Suzette whinnying]

18:13.222 --> 18:14.354
[neighs]

18:14.484 --> 18:16.573
- Hooray!
Johnny Ray!

18:16.704 --> 18:18.009
- Johnny Ray!

18:18.140 --> 18:19.837
- Johnny Ray's back!
- Yes!

18:19.968 --> 18:22.013
- [sighs]
Finally.

18:22.144 --> 18:25.191
[cheers and applause]

18:26.888 --> 18:28.063
- [whistles]

18:28.194 --> 18:30.283
That's a big audience.

18:30.413 --> 18:31.675
- Too big?

18:31.806 --> 18:34.417
- A real star
doesn't let an audience...

18:34.548 --> 18:37.594
or his friends down.

18:37.725 --> 18:39.814
Let's do this!

18:39.944 --> 18:41.381
- Hi, everybody.

18:41.511 --> 18:44.340
It's time for what we've all
been waiting for:

18:44.471 --> 18:46.777
my friend and yours,

18:46.908 --> 18:47.778
Johnny Ray!

18:47.909 --> 18:50.085
And on percussion, Suzette!

18:50.216 --> 18:51.782
[cheers and applause]

18:51.913 --> 18:52.740
- Oops.
[feedback screeches]

18:52.870 --> 18:54.176
Uh, let's see here.

18:54.307 --> 18:58.006
♪

18:58.137 --> 19:01.314
- Johnny Ray! Johnny Ray!
- Johnny Ray!

19:01.444 --> 19:03.620
- Thanks for coming, everyone.

19:03.751 --> 19:07.363
I want to sing a song for you
now called "Simple Things."

19:07.494 --> 19:09.931
This one's for my good friend
Sunny,

19:10.061 --> 19:12.542
who made tonight possible.

19:12.673 --> 19:14.022
[guitar strumming]

19:14.153 --> 19:16.111
[hooves clicking]

19:16.242 --> 19:18.418
♪ I play my guitar

19:18.548 --> 19:20.681
♪ 'Cause I like its sound

19:20.811 --> 19:22.987
♪ The way it floats
through the air ♪

19:23.118 --> 19:25.076
♪ And echoes all around

19:25.207 --> 19:26.643
♪ Soft, gentle rhythms

19:26.774 --> 19:28.689
♪ They make me want to sing

19:28.819 --> 19:32.997
♪ I really love simple things

19:33.128 --> 19:35.348
[crowd clapping to beat]

19:35.478 --> 19:39.569
♪ I don't need a crowd
or applause to want to play ♪

19:39.700 --> 19:43.573
♪ I get inspired by the things
of everyday ♪

19:43.704 --> 19:47.360
♪ The sun and breeze
and the feelings they bring ♪

19:47.490 --> 19:51.625
♪ I really love simple things

19:51.755 --> 19:53.061
♪

19:53.192 --> 19:55.324
♪ Simple things

19:55.455 --> 19:57.196
♪ Like an eagle in flight

19:57.326 --> 19:59.459
♪ Simple things

19:59.589 --> 20:01.417
♪ Or a full moon at night

20:01.548 --> 20:03.637
♪ Simple things

20:03.767 --> 20:05.987
♪ That fill you with glee

20:06.117 --> 20:10.818
♪ The simple things are
for me ♪

20:10.948 --> 20:12.602
- [whinnies]

20:12.733 --> 20:16.563
- ♪ Like when a friend
makes me laugh and smile ♪

20:16.693 --> 20:20.784
♪ Or when I get back and rest
for a while ♪

20:20.915 --> 20:24.571
♪ The simple things
are what mean the most to me ♪

20:24.701 --> 20:28.444
♪ I really love simple things

20:28.575 --> 20:33.362
♪ Yeah, how I love
simple things ♪

20:33.493 --> 20:38.976
♪ I really love simple things

20:39.107 --> 20:40.717
♪ Simple things

20:40.848 --> 20:42.241
- All right!
- Whoo-hoo!

20:42.371 --> 20:45.156
all: Johnny Ray! Johnny Ray!

20:45.287 --> 20:46.245
- Thanks.

20:46.375 --> 20:47.724
[crowd cheering]

20:47.855 --> 20:50.510
[applause]

20:50.640 --> 20:53.164
- Wow, Sunny!
I did it!

20:53.295 --> 20:54.644
- [whinnies]
- We did it.

20:54.775 --> 20:56.951
- You were amazing,

20:57.081 --> 21:00.084
and that's because you were
true to who you are.

21:00.215 --> 21:01.956
I shouldn't have tried
to change you

21:02.086 --> 21:03.218
or add to you

21:03.349 --> 21:05.438
with spoons
or ballerinas.

21:05.568 --> 21:06.439
[chuckles]

21:06.569 --> 21:07.657
I'm sorry.

21:07.788 --> 21:09.224
- Without you,

21:09.355 --> 21:12.271
I'd have never been up here
singing to a crowd,

21:12.401 --> 21:15.361
feeling like a real
country star.

21:15.491 --> 21:17.406
- Johnny Ray!
One more song!

21:17.537 --> 21:19.365
- Listen to the audience.

21:19.495 --> 21:21.280
- They want an encore.

21:21.410 --> 21:22.759
- You know, today I learned

21:22.890 --> 21:25.588
you really have to listen
to what others are saying,

21:25.719 --> 21:29.113
and I think they're saying they
want to hear you sing again.

21:30.114 --> 21:31.246
- [whinnies]

21:31.377 --> 21:34.423
[cheers and applause]

21:36.295 --> 21:38.122
- ♪ Simple things

21:38.253 --> 21:40.037
♪ Like an eagle in flight

21:40.168 --> 21:40.908
♪ Simple things

21:42.301 --> 21:43.606
- Hi, it's me, Sunny,

21:43.737 --> 21:46.435
with another look
inside the Style Files.

21:46.566 --> 21:49.220
Those country braids
look amazing.

21:49.351 --> 21:51.353
Wow!

21:51.484 --> 21:52.746
For this hairstyle and more,

21:52.876 --> 21:54.313
check out Sunny's Style Files

21:54.443 --> 21:57.054
at nickjr.com
and the Nick Jr. app.

21:57.185 --> 21:59.709
Keep smiling, keep styling.

21:59.840 --> 22:00.884
[laughs]

22:02.233 --> 22:05.106
[upbeat music]

22:05.236 --> 22:12.592
♪
